$ SQLPATH - ses
@ ses.sql

`ses.sql` selects a few rudimentary information on sessions from
→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/session[`v$session`],
→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/process[`v$process`] and
→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/sql/text[`v$sql_text`].

The value of the first returned column (sid) can be used with → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/sqlpath/kill[`kill.sql`] to terminate a session.

gh|Oracle-SQLPATH|/ses.sql||

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/sqlpath
